# Sparklab — network endpoints (Stage 6). Copy to `.env` and edit. Vite exposes VITE_* to the app.
# These are CONFIG, not code: change the broker/gateway here without touching firmware or app.

# ── MQTT broker (Tier 2, DIRECT over WebSocket — no gateway, no server of your own) ─────────────
# Default is the FREE public EMQX broker (no signup). The browser connects straight to it.
# Public brokers are SHARED + unauthenticated — fine for learning/testing; use a unique topic
# prefix and never send private data. For private/production use HiveMQ Cloud (free tier) or your
# own broker.
#   EMQX (default):       wss://broker.emqx.io:8084/mqtt
#   Mosquitto test:       wss://test.mosquitto.org:8081/mqtt
#   HiveMQ (ws only):     ws://broker.hivemq.com:8000/mqtt
VITE_MQTT_WS_URL=wss://broker.emqx.io:8084/mqtt

# ── Tier 3 gateway (OPTIONAL — only for raw-TCP-only brokers or non-CORS HTTP) ──────────────────
# A self-hosted WS→TCP relay (e.g. on your VPS). Leave blank unless you run one. It MUST enforce
# an egress allowlist (anti-SSRF). Example: wss://your-domain.example/gateway
# VITE_GATEWAY_WS_URL=

# ── Tier 3 HTTP proxy (OPTIONAL — for HTTP endpoints that do not send CORS headers) ─────────────
# VITE_HTTP_PROXY_URL=

# ── AGPL-3.0 source link ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SparkLab's own code is AGPL-3.0; section 13 requires the deployed app to offer users a link to its
# Corresponding Source. Defaults (in code) to the public repo; override here to pin a tag/branch.
VITE_SOURCE_URL=https://github.com/primeratechlabs/SparkLab-IoT-Simulation-Workstation
